import pandas as pd
import plotly.express as px

# Drop missing values
filtered_data = dataFrame.dropna(subset=["Hospital_Beds_Per_1000", "Life_Expectancy", "Country"])

# Plot with different color for each country
fig = px.scatter(
    filtered_data,
    x="Hospital_Beds_Per_1000",
    y="Life_Expectancy",
    color="Country",  #  Different color for each country!
    title="Relationship between Hospital Beds per 1000 People and Life Expectancy",
    labels={
        "Hospital_Beds_Per_1000": "Hospital Beds per 1000 People",
        "Life_Expectancy": "Life Expectancy (Years)"
    },
    trendline="ols",
    hover_name="Country"
)

fig.update_traces(marker=dict(size=8))

fig.show()
